# Rocket.new — Web Commands Reference

> ⚠️ Commands only work in the **web browser**. Not supported in the iOS app.
>
> Token tip: One specific command uses far fewer tokens than a long vague chat prompt.

---

## Two Command Types

| | `/` Commands | `@` Commands |
|---|---|---|
| What | Screen-aware shortcuts for current open page | Target a specific file or folder |
| How | Type `/` → popup → select or type to filter | Type `@` → file picker → select file/folder |
| Scope | Auto-targets the currently open screen | Locked to your selected file/folder |
| Best for | Quick actions, fixes, integrations, layout | Precise single-file or single-component edits |

---

## Web Project `/` Commands — Full List

### Brand & Identity
| Command | What It Does |
|---|---|
| `/Update App Logo` | Replace logo across all pages — attach file first |
| `/Update App Name` | Change name in titles, nav, metadata across whole app |
| `/Change App Theme` | Apply new color scheme across entire app |
| `/Add Light/Dark Theme` | Add a coordinated light/dark theme toggle |

### Layout & Content
| Command | What It Does |
|---|---|
| `/Update Content` | Replace text, copy, or placeholders on current page |
| `/Change Element` | Swap an existing element type (e.g. image → video) |
| `/Add Element` | Insert a new UI element into the current page |
| `/Remove Element` | Delete a UI element with auto layout reflow |
| `/Remove Screen` | Delete an entire page including its route and nav references |
| `/Restructure Screen Layout` | Redesign the current page's layout pattern |

