## `@` Commands — File-Scoped Edits

### How to Use
1. Type `@` anywhere in the chat input
2. File & Folders picker appears
3. Search for and select your target file or folder
4. Continue typing your instruction after the `@file` reference

### Example Patterns
```
@app/page.tsx fix the hero section — the CTA button is not linking to /signup

@components/nav.tsx add active state styling to highlight the current page link

@lib/supabase.ts add proper error handling and logging to the signIn function

@app/pricing/page.tsx change "Get started" to "Start free trial" on all three plan cards

@components/empty-state.tsx rewrite the empty state message to be more encouraging
and add a single call-to-action button linking to /create
```

### When `@` Beats Chat
- You know exactly which file needs changing
- The change is in one component and you don't want anything else touched
- You're debugging a specific function without risking the rest of the app
- Scoping a translation file update when adding languages

### `@` Troubleshooting
| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| Can't find file in picker | Type exact filename including extension and parent folder |
| Edit still affected other files | Split into smaller messages, one `@file` per message |
| Wrong file was targeted | Use the full path: `@app/dashboard/components/chart.tsx` |

---

## Phrasing Patterns That Save Tokens

**Replace specific text (most efficient):**
```
/Update Content change "Get started" to "Start free trial" in the hero section CTA button
```

**Fix a specific area:**
```
/Fix Layout Issues in the pricing grid on tablet and mobile breakpoints
```

**Insert at exact location:**
```
/Add Element add a sticky "Book a call" button in the top-right corner of the header,
visible only when user has scrolled past the hero section
```

**Scoped file fix:**
```
@components/checkout-form.tsx fix the form validation — the email field accepts
invalid formats and the submit button doesn't show a loading state
```

**Targeted content update:**
```
@app/about/page.tsx replace the team section with three cards:
Card 1: Name "Sarah Chen", Role "CEO", Bio "10 years in fintech"
Card 2: Name "James Park", Role "CTO", Bio "Previously at Stripe"
Card 3: Name "Mia Torres", Role "Head of Design", Bio "Ex-Figma"
```

---

## Command Troubleshooting

| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| Nothing changed | Confirm you're on the correct screen; for text, quote exact copy in "quotes"; name the area precisely |
| Layout still wrong after fix | Try `/Fix Layout Issues for tablet and mobile breakpoints` |
| Can't find file for `@` | Type the exact filename + extension in the picker search |
| Edit was too broad | Split into multiple `@` commands, one file per message |
| Command didn't trigger popup | Make sure `/` is at the start of the message or in the input box |

